14 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Local government requirements before funds are released. (1) To be
15 eligible to receive funding under this part, a local government other than a tribal government must establish and
16 continually fund a capital reserve account fund dedicated to capital improvement meeting the requirements of
17 subsection (3) for necessary infrastructure improvements, including but not limited to improvements to water
18 supply systems, wastewater systems, and irrigation systems.
19 (2) The capital reserve account fund dedicated to capital improvement must be established by
20 September 30 of the odd-numbered year preceding the next regularly scheduled legislative session when the
21 local government intends to receive potential funding.
